rComments: She is obviously very intelligent and well read on the law, however, she tinged everything with a political ideological bent that tainted the sanctimony of the law that should be blind. Very disappointed as I like her and respect her work. Just wish she would leave the preaching for church!

rComments: Brenda is a very compassionate and dedicated professor. She knows quite a lot about the material she teaches and she made vague areas of the law, a lot clearer.
Iwould take any course by Brenda Cossman. She is an amazing prof, she has so much knowledge and her lecture style makes it easy to take it all in.
Great Prof.  Incredibly interesting material, and entertaining lecutres.

Cossman's lecturing style is pretty sweet - informal and witty, yet thoughtful and intellectually stimulating at the same time. However, she is a terrible marker and provides little to no feedback (also impossible to get an A). Tons of reading. A valuable learning experience overall though - she's one of the best!

As a somewhat famous, accomplished lawyer, Cossman expects A LOT of precision and thoughtfulness in assignments. She seems to think she is more lenient in grading than she is. But, she's very helpful IF you go and talk to her in office hours. GO SEE HER DURING THE SEMESTER. Overall, very interesting professor, and super hot :)

Her standards are pretty high given her amazing credentials, so she doesn't really have sympathy when it comes to papers. She will criticize any and every flaw, and give you a depressingly low mark to boot. Her lectures however are entertaining, she's easy to listen to and not too bad on the eyes either!
